snippet.title: The Medians of a Triangle are Concurrent: Use Vectors! (TANTON Mathematics)
snippet.description: Vectors offer a wonderful and swift means to prove theorems in geometry. In this little video we show that the three medians of a triangle do indeed go through a common point AND we show how to find the coordinates of that point with no effort.
